When I entered the War Room, General Taddeus Azaro was in his wheelchair next to the window. Across him, Lucita was sitting with her arms crossed.

LineNo: 12341065,

Taddeus Azaro: Your Majesty.
en


"Your Majesty."

en


Judging by his face, he had not slept whatsoever. He kept his gaze on the view outside the window.

Taddeus Azaro: All my life, I was told I was mean...
en


"All my life, I was told I was meant for greatness."

en


"Once again, presenting the same news that I delivered to King Valero so many years ago."

en


"My life has been nothing but a series of failures."

en


"Yet here I am. Defeated, unworthy. I can't even stand on my own two feet."

Player_Romus: Spare me your antics.
en


"Spare me your antics."

en


"Clearly. Because, you are weak."

Player_Romus: I am sorry.
en


"I am sorry."

"Is this supposed to be a guilt trip? If it is, it is not working."

Player_Romus: There is always hope. No matter ho...
en


"There is always hope. No matter how dire the situation is."

Lucita Azaro: We have news from the frontline, Y...
en


"We have news from the frontline, Your Majesty."

Lucita Azaro: Pales still stands despite our att...
en


"Pales still stands despite our attacks on their heartland."

Lucita Azaro: The Palesian army has pushed us ba...
en


"The Palesian army has pushed us back from the border into the Pales Administrative District."

Lucita Azaro: We lost Terador and Fort Ales. The...
en


"We lost Terador and Fort Ales. The frontline is broken."

Lucita Azaro: Once we exhausted our troops, they...
en


"Once we exhausted our troops, they managed to push us back, retaking Ziqes and Arces."

Lucita Azaro: We are holding them at the border...
en


"We are holding them at the border on an equal footing."

en


"They do not seem to be currently advancing."

LineNo: 12343211,

Player_Romus: No. I have failed. This burden is...
en


"No. I have failed. This burden is mine to bear."

LineNo: 12343313,

Lucita Azaro: But our operation has failed.
en


"But our operation has failed."

LineNo: 12343415,

Narrator: Her words echoed in my head.
en


Her words echoed in my head.

LineNo: 12343541,

Player_Romus: There is no one to blame. We must...
en


"There is no one to blame. We must look to the future."

LineNo: 12343643,

Player_Romus: If not for General Azaro, we would...
en


"If not for General Azaro, we would've been celebrating our victory over Pales right now."

Player_Romus: And where were you when we were lo...
en


"And where were you when we were losing this war, Duchess?"

Taddeus Azaro: Please do not blame her, Your Maje...
en


"Please do not blame her, Your Majesty. I caused this to happen, not my daughter."

Taddeus Azaro: I know, Your Majesty. It is all my...
en


"I know, Your Majesty. It is all my fault."

Taddeus Azaro: As kind as you are, we all know, Y...
en


"As kind as you are, we all know, Your Majesty. It is all my fault."

Taddeus Azaro: No, Your Majesty. It is all my fau...
en


"No, Your Majesty. It is all my fault. I will take the blame. Not you."

Lucita Azaro: Before we figure out who is to bla...
en


"Before we figure out who is to blame, I suggest we discuss what happens next."

en


"Can we still win?"

"Should we sue for peace?"

en


"Would they be able to march on Porte Drazon?"

en


"In the light of this information, I know what needs to be done."

"I don't need to discuss anything. The path forward is clear. I know what needs to be done."

"If we keep the war going, we might eventually have an opportunity."

en


"If we sue for peace, we will lose face in the eyes of the world."

"Or they might also get their own opportunity as well."

en


"It is a risk, Your Majesty."

Lucita Azaro: I think we should keep this going...
en


"I think we should keep this going as far as we can. The international ramifications would render Rizia crippled."

"I disagree. This war can bring down Rizia along with Pales. Not to mention the resources we have already spent."

"We should sue for peace and look forward as a country."

en


"Unless the situation does not change drastically, potentially years."

Lucita Azaro: In the end, we have more resources...
en


"In the end, we have more resources than Pales. We would win the war of attrition."

en


"We would, yes. But at what cost?"

LineNo: 12347967,

Taddeus Azaro: Highly unlikely.
en


"Highly unlikely."

Lucita Azaro: But not impossible.
en


"But not impossible."

Lucita Azaro: If they keep pushing into Montakla...
en


"If they keep pushing into Montaklar, they will have access to our inner lands."

Lucita Azaro: I knew you would, Your Majesty.
en


"I knew you would, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12348375,

Lucita Azaro: What is your decision?
en


"What is your decision?"

Player_Romus: We will approach Pales to sue for...
en


"We will approach Pales to sue for peace. I do not wish any more blood to be spilled."

en


"We will continue fighting until the last drop of blood. We have to keep pushing."

en


"A sound decision, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12349073,

Lucita Azaro: Very well. Peace it is, Your Majes...
en


"Very well. Peace it is, Your Majesty."

en


"Thank you, Your Majesty."

en


"I am sorry, Your Majesty."

en


"I am sorry for failing you."

en

He turned to Lucita.

He turned his wheelchair towards me. Lucita helped him out of it.

"Command me. What are your orders?"

LineNo: 12350007,

en


He bowed deeply before me.

LineNo: 12350109,

Player_Romus: Taddeus Azaro. As befits your fail...
en


"Taddeus Azaro. As befits your failures and incompetence against the crown, I sentence you to prison."

en


I noticed the marks on his uniform where his medals used to be.

Player_Romus: Taddeus Azaro, you will leave your...
en


"Taddeus Azaro, you will leave your post immediately and relinquish all of your duties. I am de-ranking you to Colonel."

Player_Romus: You will continue to serve the Cro...
en


"You will continue to serve the Crown as you have before."

LineNo: 12350891,

Taddeus Azaro: Yes, my King. I accept the change...
en


"Yes, my King. I accept the change in my rank."

LineNo: 12350993,

Taddeus Azaro: Lucita, help me up.
en


"Lucita, help me up."

LineNo: 12351095,

en


She helped him up.

Taddeus Azaro: Thank you for your time, Your Maje...
en


"Thank you for your time, Your Majesty."

en


They left the room after bowing to me.

en

"Don't do this to yourself or us. Reconsider."

en

en

Lucita Azaro: Please.
en


"Please."

Lucita Azaro: Thank you, Romus.
en


"Thank you, Romus."

en


"Thank you, Your Majesty."

en


Lucita's eyes widened in shock.

The old mans' eyes were teary.

Signal to the guards to take them both away.
